Sentencas: One of the technical hurdles to commercialization of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) is the requirement of highly efficient cathode materials.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, we report the evaluation of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-delta (x = 0, 0.1, 0.3 and 0.5, abbreviated as SFM, SFMS1, SFMS3, and SFS) oxides as cobalt-free cathode materials of IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XPS analysis demonstrates the presence of variable valences among Fe, Mo and Sn elements, suggesting a small polaron hopping mechanism for electronic conduction.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First principle calculations reveal that SFMS3 provides the lowest average formation energy of oxygen vacancy (EvacO*) among these perovskites.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The relatively low area specific resistances are obtained with SFMS3 electrode based on La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolytes, indicating its high activity for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Power density of the single cell using SFMS3 cathode as high as 618 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C is achieved, and operation lasts for 200 h without obvious degradation.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The encouraging results promise SFMS3 as an alternative cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Novel, cobalt-free, and highly active Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5-xSnxO6-δ cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
